This paper discusses the performance of Mobile Ad hoc networks (MANET) and proposes a mathematical model to minimize the malicious behavior of mobile nodes. The topic of MANET and malicious behavior of nodes falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of malicious behavior on the overall performance of the network, which is related to the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves resource sharing and creating a consistent trust and cooperation environment, which can be related to the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the mathematical model proposed in the paper involves time division technique, which can be related to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
